  "prompt": "Does P = NP?",
  "response": "The question of whether P equals NP (P = NP) is one of the most important open problems in computer science and mathematics. P refers to the class of problems that can be solved by a deterministic Turing machine in polynomial time, while NP refers to the class of problems for which a solution can be verified by a deterministic Turing machine in polynomial time.\n\nAs of my last update in October 2023, it has not been proven whether P = NP or P \u2260 NP. Most computer scientists believe that P is not equal to NP, but no formal proof exists to confirm this belief. The Clay Mathematics Institute has designated the P vs NP problem as one of the seven \"Millennium Prize Problems,\" offering a reward of one million dollars for a correct proof either way.\n\nResearch in this area continues, and it remains a central question in theoretical computer science.",
